# Researcher — Maryland Driveway Restore (Build-Prep)

CEO decision locked: **Real WordPress site is PRIMARY**. Static HTML is fallback ONLY if Docker is unavailable on Surface.
Demo URL: `https://api.michaelwegter.com/demos/maryland-driveway-restore/` (via Flask bridge)
workSamples href: this bridge URL (NOT `import.meta.env.BASE_URL + "demos/..."`)

---

## 1. Docker Feasibility Gate (run FIRST via surface_run.py)

Send this via `python scripts/surface_run.py --lang python` before any WP build step:

```python
import subprocess, sys
r = subprocess.run(['docker', '--version'], capture_output=True, text=True)
if r.returncode == 0:
    print('DOCKER_OK:', r.stdout.strip())
    rdc = subprocess.run(['docker', 'compose', 'version'], capture_output=True, text=True)
    print('COMPOSE_OK:', rdc.returncode == 0, rdc.stdout.strip())
else:
    print('DOCKER_MISSING')
    sys.exit(1)
```

**If DOCKER_MISSING**: fall back to static HTML plan (the 9-page HTML/CSS/JS build from planner.out is complete and correct; record which fallback condition tripped). Do not attempt WP path.

---

## 2. Port Assignment

| Service | Port | Notes |
|---------|------|-------|
| WordPress container (Apache) | 8081 | bound to 127.0.0.1 only |
| MySQL container | internal Docker network only | never expose to host |

Use `127.0.0.1:8081` — not `0.0.0.0:8081` — to prevent external exposure.

---

## 3. Docker Compose Scaffold (create on Surface via runner)

Write `docker-compose.yml` to `data/runner-workspace/mdr-wp/docker-compose.yml`:

```yaml
version: "3.8"
services:
  mysql:
    image: mysql:8.0
    container_name: mdr-mysql
    restart: unless-stopped
    environment:
      MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD: mdrroot2026
      MYSQL_DATABASE: mdr_wp
      MYSQL_USER: mdr_wp_user
      MYSQL_PASSWORD: mdrwp2026!
    volumes:
      - mdr_mysql_data:/var/lib/mysql
    networks:
      - mdr-net

  wordpress:
    image: wordpress:php8.2-apache
    container_name: mdr-wordpress
    restart: unless-stopped
    depends_on:
      - mysql
    ports:
      - "127.0.0.1:8081:80"
    environment:
      WORDPRESS_DB_HOST: mysql:3306
      WORDPRESS_DB_USER: mdr_wp_user
      WORDPRESS_DB_PASSWORD: mdrwp2026!
      WORDPRESS_DB_NAME: mdr_wp
      WORDPRESS_CONFIG_EXTRA: |
        define('WP_HOME', 'https://api.michaelwegter.com/demos/maryland-driveway-restore');
        define('WP_SITEURL', 'https://api.michaelwegter.com/demos/maryland-driveway-restore');
        define('FORCE_SSL_ADMIN', false);
        if (!empty($_SERVER['HTTP_X_FORWARDED_PROTO']) && $_SERVER['HTTP_X_FORWARDED_PROTO'] === 'https') {
          $_SERVER['HTTPS'] = 'on';
        } else {
          $_SERVER['HTTPS'] = 'on'; // Always trust as HTTPS behind Flask/Cloudflare
        }
    volumes:
      - mdr_wp_data:/var/www/html
      - ./mdr-theme:/var/www/html/wp-content/themes/mdr-theme
    networks:
      - mdr-net

volumes:
  mdr_mysql_data:
  mdr_wp_data:

networks:
  mdr-net:
```

Start with: `docker compose -f data/runner-workspace/mdr-wp/docker-compose.yml up -d`

Wait ~20s for MySQL to be ready before running WP-CLI.

---

## 4. WP-CLI Setup

Install WP-CLI inside the wordpress container (exec-based approach via Docker):

```bash
# Run via docker exec in the wordpress container
docker exec mdr-wordpress bash -c "curl -sO https://raw.githubusercontent.com/wp-cli/builds/gh-pages/phar/wp-cli.phar && chmod +x wp-cli.phar && mv wp-cli.phar /usr/local/bin/wp"
```

Then all WP-CLI commands run as:
```bash
docker exec --user www-data mdr-wordpress wp --allow-root <subcommand>
```

---

