## 9. WP Theme Templates Required

Theme folder structure:
```
mdr-theme/
  style.css          # theme header
  functions.php      # enqueues, schema, nav, theme support
  index.php          # fallback
  front-page.php     # homepage: hero before/after slider, benefits, process, pricing preview, gallery preview, testimonials, FAQ accordion, estimate form
  page-driveway-restoration.php  # process, materials, restore-vs-replace cost compare, Service schema
  page-pricing.php   # 3-tier pricing table, add-ons, CTA
  page-gallery.php   # 16-24 image grid, lightbox, filter buttons
  page-about.php     # mission, ethos, team, environmental commitment
  page-faq.php       # accordion, FAQPage schema
  page-contact.php   # Fluent Forms embed, Google Map iframe, response promise
  page-service-areas.php  # MD county grid, embedded map, local keyword links
  page-free-estimate.php  # QR target: before/after, 3-bullet value prop, CTAs, minimal form
  header.php         # <head>, GA4 snippet (G-XXXXXXXX placeholder), sticky nav, sticky CTA bar
  footer.php         # footer nav, address, copyright, internal links
  assets/
    css/main.css     # full design system
    js/main.js       # before/after slider init, lightbox, FAQ accordion, mobile nav, GA4 events
```

Use `template_redirect` / `page-{slug}.php` WP template hierarchy — WP auto-selects `page-pricing.php` for the `/pricing/` page, etc. No custom page template header needed in PHP for this pattern to work.

