## 15. Surface Service Registration

Copy `scripts/surface_register_service.py`, set:
```python
NAME = "mdr-wordpress-docker"
CMD  = "docker"
ARGS = "compose -f data/runner-workspace/mdr-wp/docker-compose.yml up"
CWD  = "."   # mw-backend folder root on Surface
PORT = 8081
```

Note: `docker compose up` (without `-d`) keeps the process running, which is what `run-server.ps1` expects. The `-d` flag would exit immediately. Use foreground mode.

Actually — `docker compose up` is a long-running blocking process. The launcher (run-server.ps1) expects to own it. Register it correctly; the launcher will restart it on crash and reboot.

